al name from any of various places in Portugal named Monserrate.","Catalan: Castilianized form of <b>Montserrat</b>, from the name of a monastery located on the mountain of Montserrat in Barcelona, famous for a venerated statue of the Madonna and Child, or from a short form of the Marian name <i>Mare de Déu de Montserrat</i> ‘Mother of God of Montserrat’. Mare de Déu de Montserrat, known in English as Virgin of Montserrat, is patron saint of Catalonia. Christopher Columbus christened the Caribbean Island of Montserrat with reference to this name of the Virgin."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Aleram Monferrat was born in 1172, in Casale Monferrato, Alessandria, Piedmont, Italy, her father, Guglielmus Torresana, was 22 and her mother, Maria de Monferrato, was 19. She married Eborard de Aunus in 1187. They were the parents of at least 2 sons and 2 daughters. She died in 1195, in Combs, Suffolk, England, at the age of 23."},"et":{"1172–1195":"1172–1195","1166–1248":"1166–1248","1190–Female":"1190–Surnud","1195–1225":"1195–1225","–Male":"Surnud","1150–Male":"1150–Surnud","1153–1189":"1153–1189","1190":"1190","1248":"1248","1225":"1225","about 1190":"umbes 1190","1189":"1189","1166":"1166","1187":"1187","1153":"1153","1195":"1195","1172":"1172","1150":"1150","Casale Monferrato, Alessandria, Piedmont, Italy":"Casale Monferrato, Alessandria, Piemonte, Itaalia","Combs, Suffolk, England":"Combs, Suffolk, England","Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, England","Stow, Suffolk, England":"Stow, Suffolk, England"},"fi":{"1172–1195":"1172–1195","1166–1248":"1166–1248","1190–Female":"1190–Kuollut","1195–1225":"1195–1225","–Male":"Kuollut","1150–Male":"1150–Kuollut","1153–1189":"1153–1189","1190":"1190","1248":"1248","1225":"1225","about 1190":"noin 1190","1189":"1189","1166":"1166","1187":"1187","1153":"1153","1195":"1195","1172":"1172","1150":"1150","Casale Monferrato, Alessandria, Piedmont, Italy":"Casale Monferrato, Alessandria, Piemonte, Italia","Combs, Suffolk, England":"Combs, Suffolk, Engla